, cohesive JUnit test suite for library using AI.\n./forge/docs/functional-spec.md:36:1. **New library support** (`library-new-request`) — generate a JUnit (or\n./forge/docs/workflows/dynamic-access.md:8:The dynamic-access workflow family generates or improves JUnit/Kotlin/Scala\n./forge/docs/workflows/add-new-library-support.md:6:generates a JUnit/Kotlin/Scala test suite, produces GraalVM reachability\n./metadata/org.testng/testng/6.14.3/reachability-metadata.json:29:        \"typeReached\" : \"org.testng.junit.JUnit4TestRecognizer\"\n./metadata/org.testng/testng/6.14.3/reachability-metadata.json:71:        \"typeReached\" : \"org.testng.junit.JUnitTestFinder\"\n./metadata/org.testng/testng/6.14.3/reachability-metadata.json:73:      \"type\" : \"org.testng.junit.JUnit3TestRecognizer\",\n./metadata/org.testng/testng/6.14.3/reachability-metadata.json:83:        \"typeReached\" : \"org.testng.junit.JUnitTestFinder\"\n./metadata/org.testng/testng/6.14.3/reachability-metadata.json:85:      \"type\" : \"org.testng.junit.JUnit4TestRecognizer\",\n./metadata/org.testng/testng/6.14.3/reachability-metadata.json:97:      \"type\" : \"org.testng.junit.JUnit4TestRunner\",\n./metadata/org.testng/testng/6.14.3/reachability-metadata.json:109:      \"type\" : \"org.testng.junit.JUnitTestRunner\",\n./metadata/org.testng/testng/6.14.3/reachability-metadata.json:145:      \"type\" : \"org.testng.reporters.JUnitReportReporter\",\n./metadata/org.testng/testng/6.14.3/reachability-metadata.json:305:        \"typeReached\" : \"org.testng.junit.JUnitTestRunner\"\n./metadata/org.testng/testng/6.14.3/reachability-metadata.json:363:        \"typeReached\" : \"org.testng.junit.JUnit4TestRecognizer\"\n./metadata/org.testng/testng/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"TestNG is a JVM testing framework inspired by JUnit and NUnit that provides annotations, test grouping, parameterization, data providers, and flexible execution suites. It is used to define and run unit, integration, and functional tests for Java applications through IDE, build tool, and command-line runners.\",\n./metadata/com.sun.jersey.jersey-test-framework/jersey-test-framework-core/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Jersey Test Framework Core provides the common JUnit-based APIs and base classes for writing integration tests for Jersey JAX-RS applications. It supplies the shared client, container, configuration, and lifecycle abstractions used by the Jersey test framework's concrete container modules.\",\n./metadata/org.apache.maven.plugins/maven-surefire-plugin/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"The Maven Surefire Plugin runs a Maven project's unit tests during the test phase and reports the results. It integrates test providers such as JUnit, TestNG, and POJO-based tests with Maven's lifecycle, including options for filtering, forking, and failure handling.\",\n./metadata/org.apache.maven.plugins/maven-surefire-plugin/index.json:23:    \"description\" : \"The Maven Surefire Plugin runs a Maven project's unit tests during the test phase and reports the results. It integrates test providers such as JUnit, TestNG, and POJO-based tests with Maven's lifecycle, including options for filtering, forking, and failure handling.\",\n./metadata/com.github.sbt/junit-interface/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"JUnit Interface implements sbt's test interface for JUnit 4 so JUnit tests can be discovered and run from sbt. It is a pure-Java adapter that bridges sbt's test framework APIs to JUnit execution and reporting.\",\n./metadata/com.github.sbt/junit-interface/0.13.3/reachability-metadata.json:14:        \"typeReached\": \"com.novocode.junit.JUnitRunner\"\n./metadata/io.quarkus/quarkus-junit-common/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Quarkus JUnit Common provides shared testing support classes used by Quarkus JUnit test framework modules. It contains common JUnit integration utilities and execution conditions that are reused by the internal and public Quarkus JUnit artifacts.\",\n./tests/src/c